OL,3,CInflation holds steady but markets bet
OL,4,Cagainst August interest rate cut
OL,6,FServices prices in the UK rose by 0.6%
OL,7,Fin June alone. The rate of annual
OL,8,Fgrowth is not only unhealthily strong,
OL,9,Fbut it also beat the Bank's forecast
OL,10,Ffor the fifth consecutive month.
OL,12,FIn the Eurozone, services inflation is
OL,13,Frunning at 4.1%.
OL,15,FWhy? For reasons that my colleague,
OL,16,FMahatir Pasha, explains, the "Swift
OL,17,FEffect" is both limited and temporary.
OL,18,FThe key driver of the price of
OL,19,Fservices is typically pay growth.
